window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From two-million-selling author Joy Ellis comes one of the most eagerly awaited mysteries this year. </b></p> <p>One moonlit night, the bodies of two young people are discovered lying entwined on a blanket in the woods. The young man is clutching a red rose. It appears to be a lovers' suicide pact....</p> <p>Until Detective Nikki Galena and DS Joseph Easter look more closely. Romeo and Juliet, as they decide to call them, were murdered somewhere else and brought to the woods. But why?&nbsp;</p> <p>Then another young couple are found dead, again beautifully posed as lovers. And Nikki knows they have a twisted serial killer on their hands. Who are the next victims?&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Everyone has secrets. But some people will kill to keep them.</b></p>"; 
